<section class="content">
<h2>Data</h2>
<h3>Population Data</h3>
<p>You are free to share (i.e. to copy, to distribute and to transmit) and to remix (i.e. to adapt) the presented population data for non-commercial as well as for commercial use under the condition that &raquo;City Population&laquo; is referenced as source as follows:</p>
<ul>
	<li> <em>Thomas Brinkhoff: City Population, http://www.citypopulation.de (or the URL of the specific page)</em></li>
</ul>
<p>Instead of labelling the URL, a hyperlink should be used by web media. In other words, the <a href="http://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/3.0/" target="_blank">CC BY 3.0</a> license holds.</p>
<p>In addition, potential copyrights of the original sources (given in the tables' footnotes) must be observed (typically by specifying the source).</p>

<h3>Map Data</h3>
<p>The maps and other geospatial data are under the copyright of &raquo;City Population&laquo; and/or under the copyright of the organizations denoted at the maps. If geospatial data under the &quot;share alike&quot; (CC BY-SA) condition are used, please <a href="../contact/">contact</a> me or use the original download facilities. Coordinate data of places cannot be delivered in general.</p>

<h3>Other Data and Resources</h3>
<p>All other data and resources, which are specific for &raquo;City Population&laquo;, like images, programs and appearance are under the copyright of &raquo;City Population&laquo;.</p>
</section>

<section class="content">
<h2 id="cookies">Privacy Policy</h2>
<p>In case of using one of the websites</p>
<ul>
	<li>citypopulation.de</li>
	<li>top10cities.net</li>
</ul>
<p>&raquo;City Population&laquo; processes  personal data. In the following,  &raquo;City Population&laquo; informs about the processing of personal data in accordance to articles 12 to 14  of the EU General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR).</p>
<h3>Controller of the Processing</h3>
<p><img src="/images/impressum/responsible.png" alt="Für die Verarbeitung Verantwortlicher"></p>
<h3>Purpose and  Form of Processing</h3>
<p>&raquo;City Population&laquo; processes personal data in order to provide content and functionality of its web sites, to respond to contact requests and communicate with its users, to ensure security, to fund its offers, to measure reach and to analyze user behavior.</p>
<h4>Access Data / Server Log Files</h4>
<p>The web server collects data about every access to the websites of &raquo;City Population&laquo;. These access data include:</p>
<ul>
	<li>name of the retrieved web page, file, date and time of the access, amount of data transferred, response code, type and version of browser, the user's operating system, referrer URL (i.e. the address of the previously visited page), IP address and the requesting web provider</li>
</ul>
<p>&raquo;City Population&laquo; uses  those protocol data for following purposes:</p>
<ul>
	<li>For statistical evaluations in order to operate and optimize the web site: Statistical evaluations take place without the IP address, so that the individual user cannot longer be determined. The processing  is based on article 6 para. 1 f) GDPR; the  legitimate interest is the optimization of operation and content of the website. Due to the anonymization that has taken place, the resulting statistics do not longer allow conclusions about a user. Thus, interests or fundamental rights and freedoms of the data subject do not outweigh the aforementioned legitimate interests.</li>
	<li>For detection and elimination of dysfunctions. The processing takes place on the basis of article 6 para. 1 f) GDPR, whereby the legitimate interest lies in the safety and maintenance of the business. The processing serves to detect complex and longer-lasting attack patterns.</li>
</ul>
<p>Access data are deleted after six weeks.</p>
<h4>Cookies</h4>
<p>A cookie is a small text file that a website saves on your computer or mobile device when you visit the site. For example, it enables the website to remember your actions and preferences over a period.</p>
<p>The use of cookies takes place in the legitimate interest of »City Population« in accordance with article 6 para. 1 f) GDPR, whereby the legitimate interest lies in increasing the user-friendliness or as protection against a misuse of the website.</p>
<p>As a user, you can influence the use of cookies: browsers have an option that restricts or completely prevents the storage of cookies. In addition, already stored cookies can be displayed and deleted by the browser. If multiple browsers are used on one device, the respective settings must be made for each browser. Please note that the usage and in particular the ease of use of the website may be limited without cookies.</p>
<p>&raquo;City Population&laquo;  uses the following cookies on its own responsibility:</p>
<ul>
	<li>In order to display the note on using cookies and third-party services only on the first visit, a cookie is written when the message is acknowledged.</li>
	<li>As soon as a user modifies a setting on the page &raquo;Settings&laquo;, that setting is written to a cookie.</li>
	<li>A session cookie is written in order to prevent a misuse of the website.</li>
</ul>
<p>Additional cookies are created by the services described below without &raquo;City Population&laquo; having any direct influence on them.</p>
<h4>Google AdSense</h4>
<p>&raquo;City Population&laquo; integrates advertisements (ads) from Google AdSense on its websites. Google AdSense is a remarketing service provided by Google LLC, 1600 Amphitheater Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043, USA. It enables to offer   interest-based advertisements to visitors of a website. This service is used in accordance with article 6 para. 1 f) GDPR, whereby the legitimate interest is to refinance the costs of the website by using this type of advertisements.</p>
<p>Google AdSense uses cookies in order to  recognize users as visitors. In addition, web beacons are also used. These are invisible graphics that analyze the flow of visitors on a web page. All of this information is provided by Google to its servers in the United States. Google is <a href="https://www.privacyshield.gov/participant?id=a2zt000000001L5AAI&status=Active">certified under the Privacy Shield Agreement</a>.</p>
<p>For more information about Google's data usage, stetting and opt-out options, visit the following Google Web sites:</p>
<ul>
	<li><a href="https://www.google.de/settings/ads?hl=en" target="_blank">Information about ads personalization</a></li>
	<li><a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/ads?hl=en" target="_blank">Google privacy &amp; terms for advertising</a></li>
	<li><a href="https://policies.google.com/technologies/partner-sites?hl=en" target="_blank">How Google uses information from sites or apps that use Google's services</a></li>
</ul>
<p>&raquo;City Population&laquo; has no influence on the processing of data by Google. The accuracy of Google's information about the processing of personal data cannot be reliably verified.</p>
