<h4>Google Maps and Google Charts</h4>
<p>&raquo;City Population&laquo; uses the &raquo;Google Maps&laquo; service and includes software of &raquo;Google Charts&laquo;, both provided by Google LLC, 1600 Amphitheatre Parkway, Mountain View, CA 94043, USA. These services are used in accordance with article 6 para. 1 f) GDPR, whereby the legitimate interest is to enable the provided functionality of the website and to increase its user-friendliness.</p>
<p>By visiting a page with an integrated map based on »Google Maps« or with a chart based on »Google Charts«, your browser normally establishes a direct connection to Google's servers. This will give Google the information that your computer has accessed  that page. This also gives Google the IP address of your computer and information about your browser. Google also receives this information even if you do not have a Google account. If you are logged in to your Google account when the page is accessed, it may be possible for Google to assign this access directly to your account. If you use certain services of Google  on your device without having opted out of accessing your location data, Google may also process your location information when accessing a page that integrates &raquo;Google Maps&laquo;. It is anticipated that Google may use such information in addition to facilitating  use, optimization and prevention of misuse, also for promotional purposes.</p>
<p>You get more information by the <a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy?hl=en" target="_blank">Google Privacy Policy</a>.  &raquo;City Population&laquo; has no influence on the processing of data by Google. The accuracy of Google's information about the processing of personal data cannot be reliably verified.</p>
<h4>EOC Geoservice</h4>
<p>&raquo;City Population&laquo; uses maps of the &raquo;EOC Geoservice&laquo; provided by Deutsches Zentrum für Luft- und Raumfahrt e.V.  (DLR), Linder Höhe, 51147 Köln, Germany. This service is used in accordance with article 6 para. 1 f) GDPR, whereby the legitimate interest is to enable the provided functionality of the website and to increase its user-friendliness.</p>
<p>By visiting a page with an integrated map based on the »EOC Geoservice«, your browser normally establishes a direct connection to DLR's servers. This will give DLR the information that your computer has accessed that page. This also gives DLR the IP address of your computer and information about your browser.</p>
<p>You get more information by the <a href="https://geoservice.dlr.de/web/imprint" target="_blank">Privacy Policy of DLR</a>.  &raquo;City Population&laquo; has no influence on the processing of data by DLR. The accuracy of DLR's information about the processing of personal data cannot be reliably verified.</p>
<h4>WikiData</h4>
<p>&raquo;City Population&laquo; uses the service &raquo;WikiData&laquo; provided by the Wikimedia Foundation Inc., 1 Montgomery Street, Suite 1600, San Francisco, CA 94104, USA. This service is used in accordance with article 6 para. 1 f) GDPR, whereby the legitimate interest is to enable the provided functionality of the website.</p>
<p>By visiting a page with integrated information from the &raquo;WikiData&laquo; service, your browser normally establishes a direct connection to Wikimedia's servers (such information is marked by  <img class="wd" src="/images/wd_icon.svg" alt="" title="Wikidata Information">). This will give WikiMedia the information that your computer has accessed that page. This also gives Wikimedia the IP address of your computer and information about your browser.</p>
<p>You get more information by the <a href="https://meta.wikimedia.org/wiki/Privacy_policy/en" target="_blank">Privacy Policy of WikiMedia</a>.  &raquo;City Population&laquo; has no influence on the processing of data by WikiMedia. The accuracy of WikiMedia's information about the processing of personal data cannot be reliably verified.</p>
<h4>Further Services Called by User Interaction</h4>
<p>&raquo;City Population&laquo; integrates further services (only) after a corresponding user interaction (i.e. clicking on a  button or selecting an item from a list). These services are used in accordance with article 6 para. 1 f) GDPR, whereby the legitimate interest is to enable the provided functionality of the website and to increase its user-friendliness.</p>
<p>In case of  using one of the following services, your browser normally establishes a direct connection to a server of the corresponding service provider. This will give service provider the information that your computer has accessed that page. This also gives provider the IP address of your computer and information about your browser.</p>
<p>The following items list the services, their providers and a link to information on the purpose and extent of processing of personal data and to the user rights and  setting options:</p>
<ul>
	<li><strong>MapBox</strong> by Mapbox, Inc. (USA) &ndash; <a href="https://www.mapbox.com/privacy/" target="_blank">Privacy Policy</a></li>
	<li><strong>OpenStreetMap</strong> by OpenStreetMap Foundation (132 Maney Hill Road, Sutton Coldfield, West Midlands, B72 1JU, United Kingdom) &ndash; <a href="https://wiki.osmfoundation.org/wiki/Privacy_Policy" target="_blank">Privacy Policy</a> and <a href="https://wiki.osmfoundation.org/wiki/Services_and_tile_users_privacy_FAQ" target="_blank">Services and tile users privacy FAQ</a></li>
	<li><strong>OpenWeatherMap</strong> by OpenWeatherMap, Inc. (1979 Marcus Avenue, Suite 210, Lake Success, NY 11042, USA) &ndash; <a href="https://openweathermap.org/privacy-policy" target="_blank">Privacy Policy</a></li>
</ul>
<p>&raquo;City Population&laquo; has no influence on the processing of data by the listed service providers. The accuracy of  information about the processing of personal data cannot be reliably verified.</p>
<h4>Social Media: Web Pages and Plugins</h4>
<p>&raquo;City Population&laquo; maintains  pages within social networks and platforms in order to communicate with interested parties and users and to inform them about &raquo;City Population&laquo;. When visiting web pages of such social media networks and platforms, their terms, conditions and data processing policies hold. &raquo;City Population&laquo; integrates social-media plugins only after a user interaction (i.e. a click on a link or button) so that  <u>no data can be collected or transmitted previously</u>.</p>
<p>In the case that you want to visit web pages of a social network or to use its plugin via a corresponding link or button, you will receive information on the purpose and extent of the processing of personal data as well as on user rights and setting options via the following links to the privacy policies of social-media providers:</p>
<ul>
	<li><a href="https://www.facebook.com/policy.php" target="_blank">Facebook &ndash; Privacy Policy</a></li>
	<li><a href="https://policies.google.com/privacy?hl=en" target="_blank">Google Plus &ndash; Privacy Policy</a> </li>
	<li><a href="https://twitter.com/en/privacy" target="_blank">Twitter &ndash; Privacy Policy</a></li>
</ul>
<p>&raquo;City Population&laquo; has no influence on the processing of data by the listed social-media providers. The accuracy of  information about the processing of personal data cannot be reliably verified.</p>
<p><strong>Contacting</strong></p>
<p>When contacting &raquo;City Population&laquo; via e-mail or social media, user's details are processed  in accordance with article 6 para. 1 b) GDPR. &raquo;City Population&laquo; deletes the requests, if they are no longer required. The necessity check happens annually taking legal archiving obligations into account. At the request of a user,  an earlier deletion is possible (see below).</p>
<h3>User Rights</h3>
<p>According to article 15 GDPR a user has the right to get free information on whether personal data of the user are processed and, if so, what personal data are processed. In principle, a copy of the data may be required, unless a legal exception intervenes. In this context, information about the specific circumstances and the expected duration of the processing may also be required. Based on the knowledge of the processing of own data, the following  data-subject rights may be considered:</p>
<ul>
	<li>According to article 16 GDPR, there is a right to rectification of your personal data if  those data are incomplete or incorrect.</li>
	<li>According to article 17 GDPR, there is a right to delete one's own personal data if there is an erasure reason stated there and no  retention requirements exist.</li>
	<li>According to article 18 GDPR, the restriction of the processing of personal data can be demanded in the cases mentioned there.</li>
	<li>According to article 20 GDPR, you have the right to demand that you receive the personal data that you have provided us and to request their transmission to other responsible persons.</li>
	<li>According to article 21 GDPR, relating to your particular situation you may have the right  to object the processing of personal data.</li>
	<li>According to article 77 GDPR, you also have the right to lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority.</li>
</ul>
</section>

